The Children’s Minister has been called “woefully ignorant” by BBC presenter Emma Barnett, after he admitted he did not know how many social worker vacancies there were.
When Barnett first asked the question about the number of vacancies, Goodwill said: “I can’t give you that figure now...
You’re very fond of saying Labour benches are filled with politicians who don’t know their maths or do their sums.
@Emmabarnett has just restored a little of my faith in public service broadcasting, (by handing Robert Goodwill his arse).
@bbc5live @Emmabarnett Thank you for holding Robert Goodwill MP to account and continuing to ask important questions.
